%I A396805 #13 Jun 09 2026 14:35:34
%S A396805 1,2,33,1264,80505,7365456,893006317,136393773888,25351203412449,
%T A396805 5592284787086560,1436624546038113861,423481344402695225472,
%U A396805 141548721406753236765553,53128822864461262647331344,22211404270599760578059471565,10271826971569148623531898348416,5223579645342715413956841985430337
%N A396805 E.g.f. satisfies A(x) = x*exp( A^5(x) ).
%C A396805 Conjecture: a(n) is odd iff n is odd for n >= 1.
%C A396805 Conjecture: a(n) == [0,1,0] repeating (mod 3) for n >= 3.
%C A396805 Conjecture: a(n) == [1,2,3,4,0] repeating (mod 5) for n >= 1.
%H A396805 Paul D. Hanna, <a href="/A396805/b396805.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..200</a>
%F A396805 E.g.f. A(x) = Sum_{n>=1} a(n)*x^n/n! satisfies the following formulas, in which A^n(x) denotes the n-th iteration of A(x).
%F A396805 (1.a) A^(-1)(x) = x * exp( -A^4(x) ).
%F A396805 (1.b) A(x) = x * exp( A^5(x) ).
%F A396805 (1.c) A^2(x) = A(x) * exp( A^6(x) ).
%F A396805 (1.d) A^3(x) = A^2(x) * exp( A^7(x) ).
%F A396805 (1.e) A^n(x) = A^(n-1)(x) * exp( A^(n+4)(x) ) for all n.
%F A396805 (2.a) A(x) = x * exp( A^4(x) * exp( A^8(x) * exp( A^12(x) * ... * exp( A^(4*n)(x) * exp( ... ))))), an infinite power tower.
%F A396805 (2.b) A^2(x) = A(x) * exp( A^5(x) * exp( A^9(x) * exp( A^13(x) * ... * exp( A^(4*n+1)(x) * exp( ... ))))), an infinite power tower.
%F A396805 (2.c) A^3(x) = A^2(x) * exp( A^6(x) * exp( A^10(x) * exp( A^14(x) * ... * exp( A^(4*n+2)(x) * exp( ... ))))), an infinite power tower.
%F A396805 (2.d) A^4(x) = A^3(x) * exp( A^7(x) * exp( A^11(x) * exp( A^15(x) * ... * exp( A^(4*n+3)(x) * exp( ... ))))), an infinite power tower.
%F A396805 (3.a) A^2(x) = x * exp(A^5(x) + A^6(x)).
%F A396805 (3.b) A^3(x) = x * exp(A^5(x) + A^6(x) + A^7(x)).
%F A396805 (3.c) A^n(x) = x * exp( Sum_{k=5..n+4} A^k(x) ) for n >= 1.
%F A396805 (3.d) A^n(x) = A^m(x) * exp( Sum_{k=m+5..n+4} A^k(x) ) for n >= m+1.
%F A396805 (4.a) A(x) = A^2(x) / exp(A^6(x)).
%F A396805 (4.b) A(x) = A^3(x) / exp(A^6(x) + A^7(x)).
%F A396805 (4.c) A(x) = A^4(x) / exp(A^6(x) + A^7(x) + A^8(x)).
%F A396805 (4.d) A(x) = A^n(x) / exp( Sum_{k=6..n+4} A^k(x) ) for n >= 2.
%F A396805 (5.a) A^5(x) = log( A(x)/x ).
%F A396805 (5.b) A^6(x) = log( A^2(x)/A(x) ).
%F A396805 (5.c) A^7(x) = log( A^3(x)/A^2(x) ).
%F A396805 (5.d) A^n(x) = log( A^(n-4)(x) / A^(n-5)(x) ) for all n.
%F A396805 From _Seiichi Manyama_, Jun 09 2026: (Start)
%F A396805 E.g.f. A(x) satisfies A(x) = x*exp(A^l(x)), where A^l(x) denotes the l-th iterate of A.
%F A396805 Let a(n,k,l) = n! * [x^n] A^k(x), where A^k(x) is the k-th iterate of A.
%F A396805 a(1,k,l) = 1; a(n,k,l) = (1/(n-1)) * Sum_{i=1..n-1} i * binomial(n,i) * a(n-i,k,l) * Sum_{j=1..k} a(i,j+l-1,l). (End)
%e A396805 E.g.f.: A(x) = x + 2*x^2/2! + 33*x^3/3! + 1264*x^4/4! + 80505*x^5/5! + 7365456*x^6/6! + 893006317*x^7/7! + 136393773888*x^8/8! + ...
%e A396805 where A(x) = x * exp( A^5(x) ).
%e A396805 RELATED SERIES.
%e A396805 The series reversion of A(x) begins
%e A396805 A^(-1)(x) = x - 2*x^2/2! - 21*x^3/3! - 724*x^4/4! - 43875*x^5/5! - 3893526*x^6/6! - 461935061*x^7/7! + ...
%e A396805 where A^(-1)(x) = x * exp( -A^4(x) ).
%e A396805 The second iteration of A(x) begins
%e A396805 A^2(x) = x + 4*x^2/2! + 78*x^3/3! + 3212*x^4/4! + 213120*x^5/5! + 20031822*x^6/6! + 2476978420*x^7/7! + ...
%e A396805 where A^2(x) = x * exp(A^5(x) + A^6(x)).
%e A396805 The third iteration of A(x) begins
%e A396805 A^3(x) = x + 6*x^2/2! + 135*x^3/3! + 5988*x^4/4! + 416205*x^5/5! + 40413438*x^6/6! + 5121496359*x^7/7! + ...
%e A396805 where A^3(x) = x * exp(A^5(x) + A^6(x) + A^7(x)).
%e A396805 The fourth iteration of A(x) begins
%e A396805 A^4(x) = x + 8*x^2/2! + 204*x^3/3! + 9736*x^4/4! + 711000*x^5/5! + 71596404*x^6/6! + 9334946824*x^7/7! + ...
%e A396805 where A^4(x) = x * exp(A^5(x) + A^6(x) + A^7(x) + A^8(x)).
%e A396805 The fifth iteration of A(x) begins
%e A396805 A^5(x) = x + 10*x^2/2! + 285*x^3/3! + 14600*x^4/4! + 1121625*x^5/5! + 117424980*x^6/6! + 15797273065*x^7/7! + ...
%e A396805 where A^5(x) = log( A(x)/x ).
%o A396805 (PARI) \\ from A(x) = x * exp( A^5(x) ).
%o A396805 {a(n) = my(A=x,B,C); for(k=1, n, A = truncate(A) + x*O(x^k); B = subst(A,x,A); C = subst(A,x,B);
%o A396805 A = x * exp( subst(B,x,C) ) +x*O(x^n); ); EGF=A; n!*polcoef(A, n)}
%o A396805 {upto(n) = a(n); Vec(serlaplace(EGF))}
%o A396805 upto(25)
